-Whenever we are creating own classes we've to provide some info to the JVM about our classes like -
1. Whether this class is accessible from any other class/pkg or not 
2. Whether we can create child class
3. Whether we create Object 
-We provide this info by using Access Modifiers
Modifiers applicable for Top Level Classes - public, default, final, abstract
Modifiers applicable for Top Level Classes - All Top Level + private, protected, static


AccessModifier	withinSameCls	childClsSamePkg childClsOutsidePkg	 nonChildClsSamePkg nonChildClsOutsidePkg
Public				Y					Y				Y					Y					Y
Protected			Y					Y				**					Y					Y
Default				Y					Y				N					Y					N
Private				Y					N				N					N					N
	
	
** To access Protected Access Modifier for a child class which is outside package - Mandatory to use child class Reference.
- If wrong modifier used, then it would simply effect the visibility of Class, method or function 

